#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.57:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Upayavagga "
msgstr "6. Involvement "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Sattaṭṭhānasutta "
msgstr "57. Seven Cases "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.62, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.57:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.57:1.2"
msgid "“Sattaṭṭhānakusalo, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tividhūpaparikkhī imasmiṃ dhammavinaye kevalī vusitavā uttamapurisoti vuccati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, in this teaching and training a mendicant who is skilled in seven cases and who examines in three ways is called consummate, accomplished, a supreme person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.57:1.3"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sattaṭṭhānakusalo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a mendicant skilled in seven cases? "

msgctxt "sn22.57:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu rūpaṃ pajānāti, rūpasamudayaṃ pajānāti, rūpanirodhaṃ pajānāti, rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant understands form, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:1.5"
msgid "rūpassa assādaṃ pajānāti, rūpassa ādīnavaṃ pajānāti, rūpassa nissaraṇaṃ pajānāti; "
msgstr "They understand form’s gratification, drawback, and escape. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:1.6"
msgid "vedanaṃ pajānāti … "
msgstr "They understand feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:1.7"
msgid "saññaṃ … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:1.8"
msgid "saṅkhāre … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:1.9"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇasamudayaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇanirodhaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti; "
msgstr "consciousness, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:1.10"
msgid "viññāṇassa assādaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇassa ādīnavaṃ pajānāti, viññāṇassa nissaraṇaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand consciousness’s gratification, drawback, and escape. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.57:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is form? "

msgctxt "sn22.57:2.2"
msgid "Cattāro ca mahābhūtā, catunnañca mahābhūtānaṃ upādāya rūpaṃ. "
msgstr "The four primary elements, and form derived from the four primary elements. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:2.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called form. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:2.4"
msgid "Āhārasamudayā rūpasamudayo; "
msgstr "Form originates from food. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:2.5"
msgid "āhāranirodhā rūpanirodho. "
msgstr "When food ceases, form ceases. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:2.6"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo rūpanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of form is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "sn22.57:2.7"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.57:3.1"
msgid "Yaṃ rūpaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—"
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from form: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:3.2"
msgid "ayaṃ rūpassa assādo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:3.3"
msgid "Yaṃ rūpaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ—"
msgstr "That form is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:3.4"
msgid "ayaṃ rūpassa ādīnavo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:3.5"
msgid "Yo rūpasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—"
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for form: this is its escape. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:3.6"
msgid "idaṃ rūpassa nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn22.57:4.1"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ rūpaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpanirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya; "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known form in this way—and its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation; "

msgctxt "sn22.57:4.2"
msgid "evaṃ rūpassa assādaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpassa ādīnavaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpassa nissaraṇaṃ abhiññāya rūpassa nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipannā, te suppaṭipannā. "
msgstr "its gratification, drawback, and escape—and are practicing for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding form: they are practicing well. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:4.3"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti. "
msgstr "Those who practice well have a firm footing in this teaching and training. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.63, sc5
msgctxt "sn22.57:5.1"
msgid "Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ rūpaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpanirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya; "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known form in this way—and its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation; "

msgctxt "sn22.57:5.2"
msgid "evaṃ rūpassa assādaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpassa ādīnavaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpassa nissaraṇaṃ abhiññāya rūpassa nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādā vimuttā, te suvimuttā. "
msgstr "its gratification, drawback, and escape—and due to disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding form, are freed by not grasping: they are well freed. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:5.3"
msgid "Ye suvimuttā, te kevalino. "
msgstr "Those who are well freed are consummate ones. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:5.4"
msgid "Ye kevalino vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya. "
msgstr "For consummate ones, there is no cycle of rebirths to be found. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.57:6.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, vedanā? "
msgstr "And what is feeling? "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, vedanākāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of feeling: "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.3"
msgid "cakkhusamphassajā vedanā … pe … "
msgstr "feeling born of eye contact … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.4"
msgid "manosamphassajā vedanā. "
msgstr "feeling born of mind contact. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vedanā. "
msgstr "This is called feeling. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.6"
msgid "Phassasamudayā vedanāsamudayo; "
msgstr "Feeling originates from contact. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.7"
msgid "phassanirodhā vedanānirodho. "
msgstr "When contact ceases, feeling ceases. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.8"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of feelings is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "sn22.57:6.9"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn22.57:7.1"
msgid "Yaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—"
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from feeling: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:7.2"
msgid "ayaṃ vedanāya assādo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:7.3"
msgid "Yā vedanā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā—"
msgstr "That feeling is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:7.4"
msgid "ayaṃ vedanāya ādīnavo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:7.5"
msgid "Yo vedanāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—"
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for feeling: this is its escape. … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:7.6"
msgid "idaṃ vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn22.57:8.1"
msgid "Ye hi, keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ vedanaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ vedanāsamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ vedanānirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ vedanānirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:8.2"
msgid "evaṃ vedanāya assādaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ vedanāya ādīnavaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ abhiññāya vedanāya nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipannā, te suppaṭipannā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:8.3"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn22.57:9.1"
msgid "Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ vedanaṃ abhiññāya … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:9.2"
msgid "vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn22.57:10.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, saññā? "
msgstr "And what is perception? "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, saññākāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of perception: "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.3"
msgid "rūpasaññā, saddasaññā, gandhasaññā, rasasaññā, phoṭṭhabbasaññā, dhammasaññā. "
msgstr "perceptions of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saññā. "
msgstr "This is called perception. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.5"
msgid "Phassasamudayā saññāsamudayo; "
msgstr "Perception originates from contact. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.6"
msgid "phassanirodhā saññānirodho. "
msgstr "When contact ceases, perception ceases. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.7"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saññānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of perceptions is simply this noble eightfold path … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.8"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:10.9"
msgid "vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.64, sc11
msgctxt "sn22.57:11.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā? "
msgstr "And what are choices? "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, cetanākāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of intention: "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.3"
msgid "rūpasañcetanā … pe … "
msgstr "intention regarding sights … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.4"
msgid "dhammasañcetanā. "
msgstr "intention regarding thoughts. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.5"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā. "
msgstr "These are called choices. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.6"
msgid "Phassasamudayā saṅkhārasamudayo; "
msgstr "Choices originate from contact. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.7"
msgid "phassanirodhā saṅkhāranirodho. "
msgstr "When contact ceases, choices cease. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.8"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhāranirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of choices is simply this noble eightfold path … "

msgctxt "sn22.57:11.9"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn22.57:12.1"
msgid "Yaṃ saṅkhāre paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:12.2"
msgid "ayaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ assādo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:12.3"
msgid "Ye saṅkhārā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:12.4"
msgid "ayaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ ādīnavo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:12.5"
msgid "Yo saṅkhāresu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:12.6"
msgid "idaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn22.57:13.1"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ saṅkhāre abhiññāya, evaṃ saṅkhārasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ saṅkhāranirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya … pe … saṅkhārānaṃ nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipannā te suppaṭipannā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:13.2"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:13.3"
msgid "vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn22.57:14.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, viññāṇaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is consciousness? "

msgctxt "sn22.57:14.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, viññāṇakāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of consciousness: "

msgctxt "sn22.57:14.3"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, sotaviññāṇaṃ, ghānaviññāṇaṃ, jivhāviññāṇaṃ, kāyaviññāṇaṃ, manoviññāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:14.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, viññāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:14.5"
msgid "Nāmarūpasamudayā viññāṇasamudayo; "
msgstr "Consciousness originates from name and form. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:14.6"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho. "
msgstr "When name and form cease, consciousness ceases. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:14.7"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo viññāṇanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The practice that leads to the cessation of consciousness is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "sn22.57:14.8"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn22.57:15.1"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—"
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from consciousness: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:15.2"
msgid "ayaṃ viññāṇassa assādo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:15.3"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ—"
msgstr "That consciousness is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:15.4"
msgid "ayaṃ viññāṇassa ādīnavo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.57:15.5"
msgid "Yo viññāṇasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ—"
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for consciousness: this is its escape. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:15.6"
msgid "idaṃ viññāṇassa nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn22.57:16.1"
msgid "Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ viññāṇaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya; "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known consciousness in this way—and its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation; "

msgctxt "sn22.57:16.2"
msgid "evaṃ viññāṇassa assādaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇassa ādīnavaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇassa nissaraṇaṃ abhiññāya viññāṇassa nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipannā, te suppaṭipannā. "
msgstr "its gratification, drawback, and escape—and are practicing for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding consciousness: they are practicing well. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:16.3"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti. "
msgstr "Those who practice well have a firm footing in this teaching and training. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.65, sc17
msgctxt "sn22.57:17.1"
msgid "Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ viññāṇaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya; "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known consciousness in this way—and its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation; "

msgctxt "sn22.57:17.2"
msgid "evaṃ viññāṇassa assādaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇassa ādīnavaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇassa nissaraṇaṃ abhiññāya viññāṇassa nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādā vimuttā, te suvimuttā. "
msgstr "its gratification, drawback, and escape—and due to disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding consciousness, are freed by not grasping: they are well freed. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:17.3"
msgid "Ye suvimuttā, te kevalino. "
msgstr "Those who are well freed are consummate ones. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:17.4"
msgid "Ye kevalino vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya. "
msgstr "For consummate ones, there is no cycle of rebirths to be found. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:17.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sattaṭṭhānakusalo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is skilled in seven cases. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "sn22.57:18.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tividhūpaparikkhī hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant examine in three ways? "

msgctxt "sn22.57:18.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhātuso upaparikkhati, āyatanaso upaparikkhati, paṭiccasamuppādaso upaparikkhati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant examines the elements, sense fields, and dependent origination. "

msgctxt "sn22.57:18.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tividhūpaparikkhī hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant examines in three ways. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.57:18.4"
msgid "Sattaṭṭhānakusalo, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tividhūpaparikkhī, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye kevalī vusitavā ‘uttamapuriso’ti vuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "In this teaching and training, a mendicant who is skilled in seven cases and who examines in three ways is called consummate, accomplished, a supreme person.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.57:18.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

